---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="fraiseql-ecosystem - Strategic Analysis & Planning | FraiseQL"
  description="Meta-analysis, strategic planning, and ecosystem documentation for FraiseQL. Understand how all 11 tools work together."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>📊 fraiseql-ecosystem</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #666;">
      <strong>Strategic Analysis & Planning</strong> – Ecosystem meta-documentation
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>What It Does</h2>
      <p>
        fraiseql-ecosystem documents the strategic vision, tool relationships, and architectural decisions that underpin the FraiseQL galaxy.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Ecosystem mapping</strong>: Visual relationships and dependencies between 11 tools
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cohesion metrics</strong>: 8.5/10 ecosystem cohesion score with tool integration ratings
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Performance multiplication</strong>: How tools compound performance gains (1.2M-63M× combined speedup)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Strategic documentation</strong>: Architectural principles, design decisions, roadmaps
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Integration patterns</strong>: Best practices for using ecosystem tools together
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Why It Exists</h2>
      <p>
        Traditional GraphQL frameworks are single tools. FraiseQL is an ecosystem of 11 interconnected tools:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Hard to understand which tool solves which problem</li>
        <li>Unclear how tools work together and multiply each other's performance</li>
        <li>Integration patterns not documented systematically</li>
        <li>Strategic direction and roadmap scattered across multiple repos</li>
        <li>New users don't know where to start or how ecosystem cohesion is maintained</li>
      </ul>
      <p>fraiseql-ecosystem centralizes this strategic knowledge.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Tool Inventory</strong>: Complete catalog of 11 ecosystem projects with descriptions, performance metrics, and relationships
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Orbital Classification</strong>: Inner (essential), Mid (enhancers), Outer (supporting) tool organization
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Integration Matrix</strong>: Which tools work together, API boundaries, data flow
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Performance Stacking</strong>: How combining tools achieves exponential speedup (600× + 200K× + 2,083× + 7× = 1.2M-63M×)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Architecture Principles</strong>: Database-first philosophy, compile-time optimization, deterministic execution
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Roadmap & Vision</strong>: Multi-year strategic direction, next tools, evolution
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>The 11-Tool Galaxy</h2>
      <pre><code>{`Inner Orbit (Essential - Core Engine):
- fraiseql: Compiled GraphQL execution engine
- fraiseql-wire: 200,000× memory-efficient streaming
- confiture: 600× faster PostgreSQL migrations

Mid Orbit (Enhancers - Performance Multipliers):
- pg_tviews: 2,083× faster incremental views
- jsonb_delta: 7× faster JSONB operations
- fraiseql-seed: 300× faster test data generation
- fraisier: Canonical deployment orchestrator

Outer Orbit (Supporting - Quality & Analytics):
- fraiseql-semis: Semantic UUID test data
- fraiseql-naming-police: Naming convention enforcement
- velocitybench: 28-framework benchmarking suite
- fraiseql-ecosystem: This tool - strategic documentation`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Ecosystem Cohesion</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Cohesion Score: 8.5/10</strong> – High cohesion means ecosystem tools work together seamlessly.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql ↔ fraiseql-wire</strong>: 10/10 – Wire protocol is the default transport layer
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql ↔ confiture</strong>: 9/10 – Schema compilation → Database migrations pipeline
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql ↔ fraisier</strong>: 9/10 – Compiled schema → Deployment orchestrator workflow
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql-wire ↔ pg_tviews</strong>: 8/10 – Streaming transport optimized for large view results
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql-seed ↔ fraiseql-semis</strong>: 7/10 – Alternative approaches to test data (complementary not competing)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>velocitybench ↔ fraiseql</strong>: 8/10 – Benchmarks compare FraiseQL vs 27 other frameworks
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Performance Multiplication Chain</h2>
      <pre><code>{`Base (Traditional GraphQL Stack):        1×
+ confiture (faster migrations):        600×
+ fraiseql-wire (memory efficiency):    200,000×
+ pg_tviews (query speedup):            2,083×
+ jsonb_delta (update speedup):         7×
= Combined Ecosystem Multiplier:        1.2M - 63M×

Example: A system using all 5 optimization layers
achieves 1.2 million to 63 million times better
performance than a traditional GraphQL stack.`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Integration Patterns</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Development Workflow</strong>
          <pre><code>{`1. Author schema in Python/TypeScript decorators
2. fraiseql-cli compile schema.json
3. confiture manages → migrations
4. fraiseql-seed generates → test data
5. Local tests with fraiseql server`}</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Production Deployment</strong>
          <pre><code>{`1. Compile schema with all optimizations
2. fraisier orchestrates → deployment
3. pg_tviews refresh → automatically
4. fraiseql-wire streams → responses
5. velocitybench monitors → performance`}</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Quality Assurance</strong>
          <pre><code>{`1. fraiseql-naming-police validates → naming conventions
2. fraiseql-seed generates → consistent test data
3. velocitybench benchmarks → against competitors
4. fraiseql observability → tracks → performance`}</code></pre>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Documentation</strong>: Markdown + D2 diagrams for visual architecture
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analysis</strong>: Python scripts for ecosystem metrics and integration mapping
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Visualization</strong>: D2 diagrams showing orbital relationships and data flow
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reference</strong>: Canonical links to all 11 ecosystem projects
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Integration with Other Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>All 11 tools</strong>: This tool documents relationships and integration patterns
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql-cli</strong>: Includes ecosystem guide in documentation
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Deployment workflows</strong>: Links to fraisier, confiture, fraiseql-wire integration
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

